my bookmarks in order. There are lots of settings and features to fine tune 
the app. Great job.

I tried to install this app twice and paid for it. The app apparently  installed but there was no icon to be found so I could not start it. content: Very flexible. Works well for me

Does everything it says it does very well, the best I've found. Imported all my bookmarks (~1000 in ~100 nested folders) in one go from desktop Firefox using HTML. It worked immediately and faultlessly. The UI is clear and intuitive, though it's a shame there is so much wasted blank space at the top of the screen. Settings are excellent, allowing fine-tuning without being complex. A delight to use, got the pay version the first day. WISHLISTâ–¶â‘  When a file is exported the default filename should be amendable by the user at the point of saving. I currently have to find the file with a file manager after export to rename the file to something meaningful. â‘¡ What would make this app truly great, would be if there was an option to hold the bookmark data on SD (preferably in encrypted form), so it could be synced locally between devices (eg with Syncthing), without having to export/sync/import. PS: The bullying to update is annoying.
Great app. Usability can be further improved by handling the share intent in an overlay dialog, instead of opening a full-screen activity.
Please make it possible to sync with Dropbox or Google Drive for a big fat five starðŸŒŸðŸŒŸ

content: This is by far the best bookmark app for those who want to access their bookmarks on multiple browsers but don't want to store them in the cloud. I love the new automatic backup function.  The only improvement I'd like to see is a way to use bookmarklets.  I think they would work if there was a way open a bookmark in the current tab instead of a new tab.
It has all the features necessary and can be put to use easily and right away.The only thing needed is a bit of work on the color settings of the interface.
